  "body": "Based roughly on \r\n\r\n * https://medium.com/@weka/dividend-bearing-tokens-on-ethereum-42d01c710657 \r\n\r\nand providing an interface similar to: \r\n\r\n * https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/payment/PullPayment.sol \r\n * https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/payment/SplitPayment.sol\r\n\r\nThe specific constraints we are trying to solve (in order of priority):\r\n\r\n * The dividend disbursements can be made periodically by the contract owner, but payments are pulled to avoid iterating address mapping, optimizing the cost of gas to perform the disbursement.\r\n * The token holders can continue to use the ERC20 interfaces to trade tokens without risking missing a dividend payment or double paying dividends.\r\n * Contract owner can not collect dividends on minted tokens it holds.\r\n\r\n",
